parameters: You're finally here, It's been so long since I've seen you, Dear!
You'd never guess how happy I was to hear that you wanted to take over your uncle's old farm.
You're becoming just like you're mother, you know that?
Hehe, not that that is a bad thing, she's pretty awesome.
Aw, come give me a hug, Dear. I missed you so much!
It was probably a long drive here, wasn't it? How about I show you around, then you can rest for the night.
First stop, The barn. This is where you keep your cows.
You can graze your animals in that field. If you pull the bell inside the barn, they'll all go outside on their own.
The field is pretty bare at the moment though. You should plant grass there so that the cows have something to eat.
You can leave them outside to eat the grass on their own or you can cut it with your sickle so you can store it up for a rainy day.
You can check how much fodder you have in the silo there. Make sure you always have enough to feed you animals, okay?
Here, we have your chicken coop.
Obviously it's where you keep your chickens.
Your chickens will give you eggs everyday as long as they're fed.
You can feed them with some chicken feed you buy at the store. Just place it in the feeders on the floor.
If you have a rooster along with your chickens, you can get a fertilized egg. You can place it in the incubator to hatch the egg.
This is the docks. If you have a fishing pole, you can catch some fish for some extra money.
And that is your field for planting crops. Remember, certain crops can only grow in certain seasons, but none grow in winter.
Be sure to ship lots of crops, okay?
You can put anything you want to sell into this box, someone will come to pick it up and bring you the money.
And this will be your home for the forseeable future. Don't worry, I made sure to clean it up and add some anemities, so it's all ready for you.
I even gave you a journal for you to write in to keep track of your days. Be sure to write in it as much as you can.
Okay, how about I teach you a bit about farming then? Your ol' Momma knows her way around a farm.
Here's everything you need to get started.
Got basic tools and 5x Turnip seeds!
It should be self explanatory, right?
You use your hoe to dig into the ground then you plant the seeds. Make sure to water them everyday so they don't dry out and die.
The axe and pickaxe can be used to remove debris from your field.
Your sythe can be used for cutting down crops you no longer want or have died, and for cutting grass for fodder.
To equip tools you can either use the \i[322] and \i[323] buttons to cycle through them, or you can open your menu and equip them directly.
Tools you equip will show up in your tool hud.
To use a tool, have it equipped and press the \i[320] or the \i[326] button while standing in front of where you want to use it.
If you want to equip or items, you can do that from your menu. Items will appear in the hand slot of your tool hud.
While holding items, you can use them on different things... if it's appropriate of course.
Oh, one more thing. If you're holding food, you can eat it by pushing the \i[321], \i[324] or the \i[325] button.
Hmm... I think that's everything you need to know. You can pretty much figure out the rest by doing. You're smart.
Either way, it's getting late. I'll be leaving now so that you can rest.
Are you sure? You really don't want to let your mom teach you one more thing before letting her baby off on his own?
Honey, you're breaking my heart here.
But I suppose you really do know what you're doing.
Got basic tools and 5x Turnip seeds!
I guess I'll just leave then.

It's a bit of a test of the economy. Be sure to tell the developer if you think these prices are too cheap or too expensive, okay?
I give out money? Want some?
